  <FAQ items={[
    { question: "What LMS metrics matter most for course creators?", answer: "The four essential metrics are: (1) Enrollment-to-completion rate — shows course effectiveness; (2) Lesson engagement by content type — identifies what resonates; (3) Revenue per student — indicates pricing optimization; and (4) Cohort comparison — reveals whether changes improve outcomes. Thinkific's Engagement Dashboards track all four, while basic platforms often only provide enrollment counts." },
    { question: "How do I track student progress in an LMS?", answer: "Most LMS platforms offer multiple progress tracking methods: (1) Individual student dashboards showing lessons viewed/completed; (2) Course-level completion percentages; (3) Cohort reports comparing groups by start date; (4) Time-on-content metrics; and (5) Quiz/assignment scores. Thinkific Plus provides the most comprehensive tracking with Student Performance Dashboards showing detailed interaction history per lesson." },
    { question: "Which LMS has the best analytics for enterprise training?", answer: "Docebo and Absorb lead enterprise analytics with predictive capabilities that consumer platforms lack. Docebo's AI identifies at-risk learners before they drop out. Absorb provides compliance tracking and certification management. Thinkific Plus offers a middle ground with role-based access for team members, SCORM reporting, and engagement heatmaps suitable for mid-market training businesses." },
    { question: "Can I export LMS data to external analytics tools?", answer: "Yes. All major platforms support CSV exports of enrollment, engagement, and revenue data. Thinkific, Kajabi, and Teachable also offer native integrations with Google Analytics, Meta Pixel, and Zapier for automated data flow. Enterprise platforms (Docebo, Absorb) provide REST APIs and webhooks for real-time data synchronization with business intelligence tools like Tableau and Power BI." },
    { question: "What is SCORM reporting and do I need it?", answer: "SCORM reporting tracks compliance-focused learning metrics like pass/fail rates, time spent, and completion status for SCORM-compliant content. You need it if: (1) Your industry requires compliance documentation (healthcare, finance, aviation); (2) You purchase pre-built training content that uses SCORM; or (3) You need detailed interaction tracking for regulatory audits. Thinkific Plus includes SCORM reporting; standard plans and most consumer platforms do not." }
  ]} />

